## Filter Configuration Best Practices

**✅ DO**:

- Use kebab-case for all filter keys (e.g., `'date-range'`, `'time-range'`)
- Provide clear, descriptive labels and placeholders
- Use explicit `variant` prop for clarity
- Match filter keys to backend query parameter names
- Use `variant: 'default'` for simple dropdown selects
- Use `variant: 'multiselect'` for allowing multiple selections
- Use date/time variants for date-related filtering
- Use combobox variants for large option sets or dynamic data (single select)
- Use multiselect variants for multiple selections from large option sets

**❌ DON'T**:

- Use spaces in filter keys (e.g., `'time range'` → use `'time-range'`)
- Omit placeholder text (always provide user-friendly placeholders)
- Mix filter key naming conventions (stick to kebab-case)
- Use autocomplete for small static option sets (use `variant: 'default'` instead)
- Hard-code filter values in components (filters are configured via props)

